#Repost @corbylees2 from @northcentralshelter - TAFFY has been homeless 15 months and counting! Please SHARE to show you care she finds a family! 💞

Taffy is a cheerful sweetheart who is as delightful as soft candy. She is treat-motivated and already knows “sit” and “shake”. She would make a good companion on long walks, hiking trips or just hanging out at home. When we had her in the yard, she wasn’t keen on meeting the other dogs so we think she would prefer a home where she can be top dog. If you’re looking for an outgoing girl who loves people, please consider our sweet Taffy or TAG, COMMENT & SHARE her story to help her find a home to call her own!

Taffy is a 3 years old, spayed white and tan Pit Bull Terrier Taffy who has been at the shelter since October 11, 2016.

TAFFY #A1661820 💗🍭
-------------------
All North Central animals come spayed/neutered, microchipped and current on all their shots (including rabies). North Central LA City shelter; 3201 Lacy St., Los Angeles, CA; 213-485-5767
